<br>
After pets are able to DW without having two weapons (lvl 39, I think it is), what is the benefit of using weapons at all?<br>
<br>
I was told about lvl 15 that I would not see any benefit of giving pets weapons anymore.  Now that I'm 40, I've learned 1H weapons would have allowed them to DW much earlier, but my mage is my fun char these days.<br>
<br>
Anyway, what can I do to help my pets?  I've actually tried giving them everything from FS 2H Swords to FS Daggers/Rapiers to summoned weapons and haven't seen any difference that I could tell.<br>
<br>
Also, DOES a STR spell help pets?  We played with an lvl 39 earth pet that did 40 points without any buffs, buffed him with BO2 first and still did 40.  Gave him weapons and he did 40...added a lvl 51 druid's STR and he still did 40.  Got a kind lvl 60 shaman's STR buff and STILL only did 40.  I mean COME ON.  I could probably hit for 40 points with the lvl 60 shammie STR buff.<br>
